- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with trace inclusion and universality problems for One-Counter Nets, which are a subclass of One-Counter Automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with complexity results for decision problems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with the behavior of a specific type of automata and Petri nets, which can be used to model the behavior of programs. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of decision problems for a specific class of automata and Petri nets.
